An '''asset lock''' is a legal clause that prevents the [[asset]]s of a [[company]] being used for private gain rather than the stated purposes of the [[organisation]]. Asset locks may be incorporated into the formal structure of a "bencom" (a type of [[industrial and provident society]]), [[community interest company]], or [[charitable organisation]].

