'''Mixpanel''' is a [[business analytics]] service company. It tracks user interactions with [[web application|web]] and [[mobile app]]lications and provides tools for targeted communication with them.

Its tool-set contains in-app [[A/B testing|A/B tests]] and user [[Survey (human research)|survey]] forms.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://techcrunch.com/2014/08/27/mixpanel-ab-testing/|title = Mixpanel Adds Mobile A/B Testing To Its Analytics Platform|date = Aug 27, 2011|website=TechCrunch|accessdate = }}</ref> Data collected is used to build custom reports and measure [[user engagement]] and retention.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://allthingsd.com/20121217/andreessen-and-mixpanel-call-for-an-end-to-bullshit-metrics/|title = Andreessen and Mixpanel Call for an End to "Bullshit Metrics"|date = Dec 17, 2012|website=AllThingsD|accessdate = }}</ref> Mixpanel works with web applications, in particular [[Software as a service|SaaS]], but also supports mobile apps.

==History==
Mixpanel was founded by Suhail Doshi and Tim Trefren in 2009 and is based in San Francisco, California.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/mixpanel|title = Mixpanel profile on CrunchBase|website=CrunchBase|date = }}</ref> It is backed by [[Y Combinator (company)|Y Combinator]], and its list of investors includes [[Andreessen Horowitz]],<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://blogs.wsj.com/venturecapital/2014/12/18/mixpanel-raises-65-million-to-build-predictive-data-tech/|title = Mixpanel Raises $65 Million to Build Predictive Data Tech|date = Dec 18, 2014|website=The Wall Street Journal|accessdate = }}</ref> [[Max Levchin]] and [[Keith Rabois]].<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://techcrunch.com/2012/05/10/mixpanel-andreessen-horowitz/|title = Mixpanel Raises $10.25M Led By Andreessen Horowitz, Now Provides Analytics For Viddy And Path|date = May 10, 2012|website=TechCrunch|accessdate = }}</ref>

In April 2018, founder and CEO Suhail Doshi announced he would step down and become chairman of the board. He was replaced as CEO by Amir Movafaghi.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/04/23/mixpanel-amir-movafaghi-ex-twitter-replaces-suhail-doshi-as-ceo.html|title=Twitter's former 'Mr. Fixit' takes over analytics start-up Mixpanel as 29-year-old CEO steps down|last=Levy|first=Ari|date=2018-04-24|work=CNBC|access-date=2018-04-24}}</ref>

